#: src/auto-frontlight.md:3
msgid ""
"Cadmus can automatically adjust your frontlight's warmth and brightness "
"throughout the day based on the position of the sun at your location."
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:8
msgid ""
"When enabled, Cadmus runs a background task that recalculates the ideal "
"frontlight levels every **5 minutes** and applies them immediately. The "
"first adjustment happens as soon as the feature starts, and then repeats on "
"every 5-minute mark."
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:12
msgid "The adjustment has two dimensions:"
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:14
msgid ""
"**Warmth** – zero warmth during the day, gradually ramping up to full warmth "
"over a 1.5-hour window around sunset, staying at full warmth through the "
"night, then ramping back down to zero over the 1.5-hour window before "
"sunrise."
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:17
msgid ""
"**Brightness** – unchanged during the day (keeps whatever level you last "
"set). After sunset brightness drops to `auto-frontlight-night-brightness` "
"and stays there until sunrise."
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:21
msgid "Enabling automatic adjustment"
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:23
msgid "Open **Main Menu → Settings → General** and turn on **Auto Frontlight**."
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:25
msgid "You can also enable it directly in your settings file:"
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:31
msgid ""
"See [`auto-frontlight`](settings/index.md#auto-frontlight) and related "
"entries in the Settings reference for all available options."
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:34
msgid "Manual adjustments pause automation"
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:36
msgid ""
"If you manually change the frontlight level while automatic adjustment is "
"running, Cadmus stops the background task so your chosen level is preserved. "
"Automatic adjustment resumes the next time the app is started."
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:40
msgid "Location detection"
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:42
msgid ""
"Sun position is calculated from your geographic coordinates. Cadmus obtains "
"these automatically during each [time sync](time-sync.md): the same "
"`ipapi.co` lookup that resolves your timezone also returns a latitude and "
"longitude, which are saved to `auto-frontlight-last-coordinates` in your "
"settings file."
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:47
msgid ""
"If no coordinates are available yet (for example, before the first "
"successful time sync), automatic adjustment is skipped until a location is "
"known."
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:50
msgid "Manual coordinates override"
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:52
msgid ""
"If you prefer not to rely on IP-based location, or if the detected location "
"is inaccurate, you can set your own coordinates:"
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:59
msgid "Manual coordinates take priority over auto-detected ones."
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:61
msgid ""
"You can also edit this in **Main Menu → Settings → General** under **Auto "
"Frontlight Manual Coordinates**."
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:64
msgid "Night brightness"
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:66
msgid ""
"The brightness level used after sunset defaults to `1.0` (1%). You can raise "
"this if you find the screen too dim for nighttime reading:"
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:73
msgid "The value is a percentage from `0.0` to `100.0`."
msgstr ""

#: src/auto-frontlight.md:77
msgid ""
"\\[!NOTE\\] When [automatic time syncing](time-sync.md) is enabled, a "
"request is sent to `ipapi.co` to resolve your timezone. That same response "
"includes an approximate latitude and longitude derived from your public IP "
"address, which Cadmus stores as `auto-frontlight-last-coordinates`."
msgstr ""

